(153, 1, '2024-02-13 14:13:16', '2024-02-13 14:13:16', '<!-- wp:cover {\"url\":\"http://localhost/PSWordpress/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/staying-positive.jpg\",\"id\":152,\"dimRatio\":50,\"layout\":{\"type\":\"constrained\"}} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-cover\"><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"wp-block-cover__background has-background-dim\"></span><img class=\"wp-block-cover__image-background wp-image-152\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://localhost/PSWordpress/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/02/staying-positive.jpg\" data-object-fit=\"cover\"/><div class=\"wp-block-cover__inner-container\"><!-- wp:paragraph {\"align\":\"center\",\"placeholder\":\"Write title\",\"fontSize\":\"large\"} -->\n<p class=\"has-text-align-center has-large-font-size\">Suitable for 0-18 years</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:cover -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\" id=\"being-in-the-moment-why-it-s-good-for-parent-child-relationships\">Being in the moment: why its good for parent-child relationships<a></a></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Being in the moment is about&nbsp;<strong>tuning in and thinking about whats going on with your child</strong>. It shows your child that you care about the things that matter to them, which is the basis for a strong relationship.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Here are&nbsp;<strong>ideas for being in the moment</strong>&nbsp;with your child:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Show acceptance, let your child be, and try not to give directions all the time. If your child wants to pretend the building blocks are people, thats OK. You dont have to get your child to use them the right way.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Notice what your child is doing and encourage it without judgment. For example, Are the big blue blocks the shopkeepers? And is the little red block going shopping?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Listen to your child and tune in to their feelings. For example, if your child is telling you a long story about what happened during the day, they might really be saying that they had a happy day.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Stop and think about what your childs behaviour is telling you. For example, if your teenage child is hanging around in the kitchen but not talking much, they might just want to be close to you. You could offer a hug or let them help with dinner, without needing to talk.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Part of being in the moment with your child is&nbsp;<strong>giving your child opportunities to take the lead</strong>. For example:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><a href=\"https://raisingchildren.net.au/toddlers/play-learning/getting-play-started/letting-your-child-lead-play\">Let your child lead play</a>&nbsp;by watching your child and responding to what your child says or does. This is great for younger children.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Support your childs ideas. For example, if your older child decides to plan a family meal, why not say yes?</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>When your child expresses an opinion, use this to learn more about your childs thoughts and feelings, even if theyre different from yours.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/277027243?h=64b614e110\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"vimeo\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://player.vimeo.com/video/277027243?h=64b614e110\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed -->', 'Positive relationships for parents and children: how to build them', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '9-revision-v1', '', '', '2024-02-13 14:13:16', '2024-02-13 14:13:16', '', 9, 'http://localhost/PSWordpress/wordpress/?p=153', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
